Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop them onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, reserve 1 @baby gem lettuce{1}(leaf) per person. Trim the remaining @baby gem lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly slice widthways.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on a medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @British streaky bacon{6%rashers} and fry until crispy and brown, ~{3-4%minutes} on each side, then transfer to a #plate{}.

Return the pan to medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{} if needed. Add the sliced onion and cook, stirring frequently, until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, then transfer to a #bowl{}.

Meanwhile, add the @British pork and oregano sausage meat{225%grams} to a large bowl and season with @pepper{}. Mix together with your hands.

Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Wipe out the (now empty) frying pan and pop back on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the burgers and fry until browned and cooked through, ~{5-6%minutes} on each side. Carefully turn them every 2 mins and lower the heat if needed.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

When the burgers are cooked, remove the pan from the heat. Carefully place the @onion marmalade{22.5%grams} and cheese on top of the burgers. Cover with a #lid{} (or foil), then set aside, off the heat, to allow the cheese to melt, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Grate the @apple{1}(grated, no need to peel), then pop it into a #medium bowl{} with the @coleslaw mix{120%grams}, chopped baby gem and three quarters of the @mayonnaise{32%grams}. Mix together and season to taste.

When the wedges have 5 mins left, chop 1 rasher of crispy bacon per person. Halve the @burger buns{2}.

Sprinkle the bacon and remaining cheese over the wedges, then return to your oven for the remaining time until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, pop the burger buns into the oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the bun bases with the remaining mayo. Top with a reserved lettuce leaf, cooked onions, cheesy burgers and remaining bacon rashers. Sandwich shut with the bun lids. Serve the cheesy bacon wedges and apple slaw alongside. Enjoy!